#ident	"@(#)bnu.admin:Helpdev_r	1.4"

ABSTRACT:
	The remove task allows you to prune the list of devices over which your
	system can initiate communication with other systems.  A device may
	be a directly connected host, a modem, or a TLI network interface.

ddrm:Device type
	Choose the type of device that Basic Networking should no longer
	use for accessing remote systems.  Device information will be
	listed for your confirmation before removal.

dprm:Port
	Choose the port of a device that Basic Networking should no longer
	use for accessing remote systems. Device information will be listed
	for your confirmation before removal.

